            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-history"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has no known chronic medical conditions and is up to date on routine childhood immunizations. She has no prior hospitalizations and no history of inflammatory bowel disease, chronic diarrhea, or abdominal surgery. Her current illness began about 18 hours ago with nausea and abdominal cramping, followed by repeated watery diarrhea and a few episodes of non-bilious, non-bloody vomiting. Oral intake has decreased, and urine output is slightly reduced today.\n\nRelevant lifestyle and exposure history includes recent attendance at a community picnic and possible sick contact with both her brother and other children with recent gastrointestinal symptoms. There has been no recent international travel, no known exposure to untreated water, and no recent antibiotic use. She normally eats a varied diet, is physically active, and has had normal growth and development.\n\nShe has never required IV fluids, and there is no personal history suggesting appendicitis, diabetes, or immune compromise. The main comorbidity risk in this presentation is mild dehydration related to gastrointestinal fluid losses."
          }
        ]
      }
